text: Hacienda San Francisco, also known as Hacienda Quilichini, is a sugar mill complex with hacienda house that was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1995. The sugar mill was built in 1871. The hacienda house and a mill are regarded as contributing buildings; there are also a kitchen, a shed, a water tower, and some other buildings. with ==References== Category:National Register of Historic Places in Puerto Rico Category:Buildings and structures completed in 1871 Category:Grinding mills in Puerto Rico Category:Grinding mills on the National Register of Historic Places
